PICU VidyoDesktop™ Log in Instructions

Basic instructions to log in to VidyoDesktop™.

  1. Right mouse click the gray VidyoDesktop™ application icon located in the Windows taskbar (lower right corner of the screen) to display the pop-up menu.

  2. Select "Log in" from the pop-up menu.

PICU VidyoDesktop™ Start Recording Instructions

Basic instructions to start recording a VidyoDesktop™ conference with the Reach Transport team from the PICU Command Center Windows 7 desktop computer.

  1. Right mouse click the full-color VidyoDesktop™ application icon located in the Windows taskbar (lower right corner of the screen) to display the pop-up menu.

  2. Select "Manage Account" from the pop-up menu.

  3. Click "Home" from the Vidyo™ Portal web page navigation menu.

  4. Click "PICUTransport" from the "My Contacts" tab on the Vidyo™ Portal web page.

  5. Click the "Join Room" button on the Vidyo™ Portal web page to start the video conference. (NOTE: This will open a new window for the video. Navigate back to the web portal to continue.)

  6. Click "Control Meeting" from the Vidyo™ Portal web page navigation menu.

  7. Click "PICUTransport" to select the Room to record.

  8. Click the record button icon to start recording.

  9. Select "STANDARD-QUALITY" from the pop-up menu.

PICU VidyoDesktop™ Stop Recording Instructions

Basic instructions to stop recording a VidyoDesktop™ conference with the Reach Transport team from the PICU Command Center Windows 7 desktop computer.

  1. At the conclusion of the video conference, click the record button icon again to stop recording.
